# migrated from tests/cases/chitchat.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test chitchat]
# gen125 (chatsim-pulled): the AFFECTIVE / phatic register. The sim transcripts
# were full of casual social moves parrot0 could only meet with the bare wall —
# laughter and emoji, frustration at its own repetition, encouragement, banter,
# offers to switch language, filler. mod_chitchat (last in the registry) answers
# the TONE in register, honestly admitting parrot0 is small and never claiming to
# have parsed the content. It fires ONLY on a real affective cue, so genuine
# content questions still get the honest wall.

# Frustration at the bot's repetition -> honest acknowledgement of limits.
> you keep saying the same thing
< I know I repeat myself — I'm a small bot and honest about my limits. What would you like to try?

# Encouragement -> gracious, honest.
> no worries, you will learn
< Thanks — I'm learning as we go.

# An offer to switch language -> meet it in register.
> can we talk in italian instead
< We can chat in either language — I'll do my best.

# Conversational filler -> light engagement, not a wall.
> just bored, nothing much
< Happy to just chat. Tell me a little, and I'll follow the thread as best I can.

# Agreement with parrot0's self-description -> acknowledge and move on.
> fair enough, makes sense
< Glad that lands. What would you like to do next?

# Generic affective contact (emoji) -> in-register engagement (the generic reply
# rotates across turns so it never becomes a broken record; this is turn 6).
> squawk 🦜
< I'm enjoying this — what's on your mind?

# Anti-impostor: a real knowledge question carries no affective cue, so it still
# gets the honest wall — chitchat must never swallow genuine questions.
> is the sky blue?
< I don't understand that yet.

# gen140: companion-style casual conversation. These are non-technical,
# non-knowledge turns from ordinary users; answer naturally without pretending
# to know facts or feelings.
> i don't know what to say
< We can start simple: tell me something about your day, or ask me to remember or reason about a small fact.
> tell me something
< We can start simple: tell me something about your day, or ask me to remember or reason about a small fact.
> can we just talk
< Happy to just chat. Tell me a little, and I'll follow the thread as best I can.
> im tired
< Sounds like a low-energy moment. We can keep it light — tell me one thing that happened, or ask me something small.
> that's cool
< Nice. Tell me what made it good, or give me a small thing to reason about.

# gen140 stress set: ten casual/non-technical openings, all should avoid the wall
# while staying honest and steering toward a tractable conversation.
> no idea what to say
< We can start simple: tell me something about your day, or ask me to remember or reason about a small fact.
> say something
< We can start simple: tell me something about your day, or ask me to remember or reason about a small fact.
> entertain me
< We can start simple: tell me something about your day, or ask me to remember or reason about a small fact.
> rough day
< Sounds like a low-energy moment. We can keep it light — tell me one thing that happened, or ask me something small.
> bad day
< Sounds like a low-energy moment. We can keep it light — tell me one thing that happened, or ask me something small.
> just talk
< Happy to just chat. Tell me a little, and I'll follow the thread as best I can.
> lets talk
< Happy to just chat. Tell me a little, and I'll follow the thread as best I can.
> im happy
< Nice. Tell me what made it good, or give me a small thing to reason about.
> great day
< Nice. Tell me what made it good, or give me a small thing to reason about.
> cool
